[b]ST-62 Battle Station[/b]\par
\par
Where the ST-60 only carries a defensive armament to discourage attacks, the ST-62 Battle Station is designed specifically for combat. These massive spaceborne fortifications are deployed to protect critical front-line targets. Their heavy laser arrays and quantum torpedo launchers can rapidly demolish even dreadnoughts, and their armor is thick enough to shrug off all but the most focused attacks. Now and then a senior UGTO admiral gets it into his head to use one of these battle platforms offensively, but many find out the hard way that it can be incredibly risky. The huge size of these stations makes it difficult to withdraw them once committed to battle, a flaw that the Confederate Navy has repeatedly exploited to devastating success.\par
